<span class="c"># What each service actually means.</span></code></pre>
      <h2>What You're Getting</h2>
    </div>
    <%= render Card.new(variant: "grid") do %>
      <div>
        <pre><code class="highlight"><span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">email_support</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nv">subj: </span><span class="p">,</span><span class="nv"> body: </span><span class="p">)</span></code></pre>
        <p>A direct inbox read by the people who write JRuby. Not a ticketing system, not a chatbot — an actual person who can commit a fix the same day they read your message. All tiers.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <pre><code class="highlight"><span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">release_notify</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nv">changelog: </span><span class="p">)</span></code></pre>
        <p>Advance notice of upcoming JRuby releases, security patches, and breaking changes before they're public. Enough lead time to test against your application and plan your rollout. All tiers.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <pre><code class="highlight"><span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">chat_support</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nv">medium: :any</span><span class="p">)</span></code></pre>
        <p>Real-time conversations via text, video, or screen share with a core developer. Scheduled when it works for your team. Expert includes 1 hour/month; Enterprise is unlimited.</p>
